{
  "stem": "753.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At a time of the harvest, I was helping them and, of course, getting some fruit and taking it home.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I would go, let's say, to a place where the harvest was, and I would get acquainted with somebody, right away, I run away and never came back because I didn't want to be questioned, who we are and what we are.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I read a lot.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were hermetically isolated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had no clue what was going on the front.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had nowhere to, to read, only propaganda from the newspaper.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We did not have money to buy the newspaper-- if we would see it somewhere.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had no clue how close the end was.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I have to tell you that when the front passed through our village already-- this was 1945-- and the Germans were retreating in rags, we were still hiding.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We still did not get out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Until one day-- and here I have to say that probably half of the village must have known that we are Jewish.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But they were not telling each other.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were such noble people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because when, one day, an armored, big truck stopped in front of the house where we lived, and Palestinian young men jumped out of that armored car with Magen David here, they were looking for Jews.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Probably somebody showed them where we are.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that's how they liberated us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was that end.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was May, 1945, for us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1945, in May, when they came, it looked to me like a Fata Morgana or whatever, having-- seeing somebody with the [LAUGHS] Magen David.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And here we were two years living in a different identity.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And for me, the transition to freedom was very hard.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
